HEADWORD: mechanization
<hw>mechanization</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process
of mechanizing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Causing to be performed by machines, especially by a
highly technical implementation, usually involving electronic hardware;
<as>as, the <ex>mechanization</ex> of a manufacturing
process</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> automation, mechanisation, high technology,
high-tech.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mechanize</ent>⟦br⟧
